.TH FINDREPOS 1 "October 2024" "Version %VERSION%" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
findrepos \- Recursively search for Git repositories

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B findrepos
[startdir]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B findrepos
is a simple utility that recursively searches for Git repositories starting from the specified directory (or the current directory if none is provided). It outputs the paths of all found repositories.

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B startdir
The starting directory from which to begin searching. If not specified, the current directory is used.

.SH EXAMPLES

.TP
.B findrepos
Search for all Git repositories starting from the current directory and output their paths.

.TP
.B findrepos /home/git
Search for all Git repositories under the `/home/git` directory and output their paths.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gitin(1),
.BR gitin.conf(5)

